<TITLE> 6 JMB men get life for Sherpur serial bombing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sherpur, Sep 3 (bdnews24.com)A court has convicted six Jama'atul Mujahideen Bangladesh militants of the series bomb attacks in Aug 2005 in Sherpur and sentenced them to life in prison. Judge Mohammed Murshid Alam of the Senior Special Judge's Court of Sherpur delivered the verdict on Thursday after taking the deposition of 58 witnesses. The convicts are JMB Dhaka divisional commander, sentenced to death in another case, Salahuddin alias Salehin, 40, JMB Sherpur district commander Mujahidul Islam Sumon, 27, his brother Nazmul Hasan Ruman, 35, Abdul Mannan, 38, Rafiqul Islam, 20, and Mustafizur Rahman alias Zahid alias Lincoln, 35. They were fined Tk 25,000 each and will serve another year in prison if unable to pay. Among them, Mannan, Lincoln and Rafiqul Islam are at large but others were present at the court when the verdict was delivered. Another defendant, Humaun Kabir Shawkat, 22, was acquitted for lack of evidence. Defence lawyer Touhidur Rahman said they are going to appeal in the higher court. On Aug 17, 2005, JMB members carried out synchronised bomb attacks from 11:05am to 11:10am on Sherpur District Judge's Court premises, deputy commissioner's office premises, New Market, and Naohata and Gouripur bus terminals. A case had been filed by Mokhlesur Rahman, then the assistant sub-inspector of Sherpur Sadar Police Station, after the incident. After the investigation, police pressed charges in court against nine people including JMB chief Shaykh Abdur Rahman and Siddiqul Islam Bangla Bhai, who were hanged in 2006 in other cases. Chandan Kumar Pal fought the case for the state. bdn
